# Git workflow

Read [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) for full details.

## Branches

- `main` — protected, squash-merge only
- `feat/<topic>`, `fix/<topic>`, `chore/<topic>`, `hotfix/<version>`
- Never force-push `main`

## Commits

- Conventional Commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `chore(scope):`, etc.
- Commit after local `lint` + affected tests pass
- Never commit secrets, `.env`, or hand-edited `schemas/`
- Agents: **do not create git commits unless the user explicitly asks**

## Pull requests

- PR title = squash commit message (Conventional Commit format)
- Reference issues: `Fixes #N` or `Refs #N`
- User-facing changes need `.changeset/*.md` in the same PR
- New features: check [ROADMAP.md](../../ROADMAP.md) alignment

## Changesets

Add a changeset file with every user-facing PR. Run `bun run changeset` when needed.
